    Examples

    Examples.Rmd
    library(datamations)
library(dplyr)

    group_by()

    One grouping variable 

    "small_salary %>%
  group_by(Work)" %>%
  datamation_sanddance()

    Two grouping variables 

    "small_salary %>%
  group_by(Work, Degree)" %>%
  datamation_sanddance()

    Three grouping variables 

    library(palmerpenguins)

"penguins %>%
  group_by(sex, island, species)" %>%
  datamation_sanddance()

    summarise()

    mean of a variable 

    "small_salary %>%
  group_by(Work) %>%
  summarise(mean_salary = mean(Salary))" %>%
  datamation_sanddance()

    Other summary functions 

    "small_salary %>%
  group_by(Work) %>%
  summarise(median_salary = median(Salary))" %>%
  datamation_sanddance()

    filter()

    Filtering initial data 

    "small_salary %>%
  filter(Salary > 90)" %>%
  datamation_sanddance()

    Filtering within groups 

    "small_salary %>%
  group_by(Work) %>%
  filter(Salary == mean(Salary))" %>%
  datamation_sanddance()

    Filtering after summarize 

    "small_salary %>%
  group_by(Work) %>%
  summarise(median_salary = median(Salary)) %>%
  filter(median_salary > 90)"  %>%
  datamation_sanddance()

    count() 

    "small_salary %>%
  count(Work)" %>%
  datamation_sanddance()
